ZH: 我提前借给他1000元，以免他在旅途中用不完。
EN: I lent him 1000 yuan in advance so that he wouldn't run out of money during the trip.

ZH: 要记住备份你的文件，以免意外造成数据丢失。
EN: Remember to back up your files to avoid data loss in case of unexpected events.

ZH: 请戴上口罩，以免传播疾病。
EN: Please wear a mask to prevent the spread of diseases.

ZH: 他经常早起锻炼，以免变得身体虚弱。
EN: He exercises in the morning regularly to avoid becoming physically weak.

ZH: 喝温水可以保持身体温暖，以免感冒。
EN: Drinking warm water helps keep the body warm to avoid catching a cold.

ZH: 他认真学习每个字的发音，以免发音错误。
EN: He studies the pronunciation of each word carefully to avoid making mistakes.

ZH: 在写作文之前，先列出要点，以免遗漏重要内容。
EN: Before writing an essay, make a list of key points to avoid missing important content.

ZH: 请检查行李是否锁好，以免东西丢失。
EN: Please check if the luggage is securely locked to prevent things from being lost.

ZH: 要注意时间，以免迟到。
EN: Pay attention to the time to avoid being late.

ZH: 在烹饪之前，先准备好所有食材，以免临时乱忙。
EN: Prepare all the ingredients before cooking to avoid being rushed at the last minute.

ZH: 请把你的手机号码告诉我，以免失去联系。
EN: Please give me your phone number so we don't lose contact.

ZH: 下雨天要小心开车，以免发生交通事故。
EN: Drive carefully on rainy days to avoid traffic accidents.

ZH: 在收到邮件后及时回复，以免让对方等待。
EN: Reply promptly after receiving an email to avoid keeping the other person waiting.

ZH: 在夏天穿适合的衣服，以免中暑。
EN: Wear appropriate clothes in summer to avoid heatstroke.

ZH: 要认真检查作业，以免出现错误。
EN: Check the homework carefully to avoid mistakes.

ZH: 在旅行前预订酒店，以免没有住的地方。
EN: Reserve a hotel before the trip to avoid having nowhere to stay.

ZH: 学生应该按时完成作业，以免给老师添麻烦。
EN: Students should complete their assignments on time to avoid causing trouble for the teacher.

ZH: 需要努力工作，以免被别人抢走机会。
EN: Need to work hard to avoid having opportunities taken away by others.

ZH: 在外出时要随身携带证件，以免发生意外。
EN: Carry identification documents with you when going out to avoid accidents.

ZH: 要及时缴纳水电费，以免影响供应。
EN: Pay water and electricity bills in a timely manner to avoid supply disruptions.
